<h2>Free Does Not Mean Inaccurate</h2>
<p>The tax calculations in this free tool use the same methodology as paid payroll services:</p>

<p>Federal income tax uses the IRS percentage method from Publication 15-T, with the 2024 standard deduction applied before bracket rates. Social Security applies at exactly 6.2% and stops at the $168,600 annual cap. Medicare applies at 1.45% with no cap. State income taxes are calculated from each state's actual 2024 withholding tables -- not approximations.</p>

<p>A pay stub with inaccurate tax calculations raises red flags with experienced reviewers. This tool produces numbers that match what a payroll processor would generate, which is what makes the stub credible.</p>

